	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002339_0001"/><!--pb/@n='78r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right">17 June 1865</p><!--<p rend="right"><placeName>Botanic Garden.</placeName></p>
<p rend="right">Oxford.</p>
-->
<lb/><p> My dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I send you by 
<lb/>book post the 
<lb/>last sheet &amp; preface 
<lb/>corrected &amp; all 
<lb/>ready for press. 
<lb/>They came to me 
<lb/>on Wednesday 
<lb/>but I have been 
<lb/>immersed in the 
<lb/>dissipation of 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002339_0002"/><!--pb/@n='78v'-->
<lb/><placeName>Oxford</placeName> &amp; could not 
<lb/>look on them till 
<lb/>today. I think that 
<lb/>I shall stay over 
<lb/>Wednesday to the 
<lb/>commemoration<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I gave a little lecture 
<lb/>in <persName>D<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Daubeney's</persName>
<lb/>lecture room last 
<lb/>night. I would 
<lb/>have got the 
<lb/>Theatre but it 
<lb/>takes so much out 
<lb/>of me to prepare 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002339_0003"/><!--pb/@n='79r'-->
<lb/>for a big audience. 
<lb/>I am glad I had the 
<lb/>excuse that I 
<lb/>could not give 
<lb/>the necessary few 
<lb/>days notice<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">David Livingstone</p>
			
</div>
